Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.progress.reporters

Class Progress

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.messaging.broadcasters.Multicaster
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.progress.reporters.Progress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Resettable, Transmitter<Transmittable>, NamedObject, PackagePathed, ProgressReporter, Broadcaster, Transceiver
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcurrentProgress
    public class Progress
extends Multicaster
implements ProgressReporter
    A progress reporter that sends progress messages to a Listener as an operation proceeds. Progress reporting on an operation is started with start(String). At each step, next() or next(long) should be called to report progress. When the operation is over end(String) should be called.

    Example - Broadcasting Progress of an Operation 

     var progress = Progress.create(LOGGER, "bytes");
 progress.start("Downloading")
 while ([...])
 {
     [...]

     progress.next();
 }
 progress.end("Downloaded");

    Example - Listening to the Progress of an Operation 

     progress.listener(percent -> System.out.println("$ complete", percent);
    Progress is not thread-safe. To report progress in a multi-threaded operations, use ConcurrentProgress.
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
